{"from":"manager","to":"eng-1-1","body":"TASK 10 (CRITICAL PATH): Implement src/search.py + tests/test_search.py\n\nAll dependencies are on main (movegen, evaluation, move_ordering). Pull main first: git merge main\n\nCreate src/search.py with:\n\ndef search(board: Board, time_limit: float) -> int:\n    Returns best encoded move using iterative deepening + alpha-beta.\n\nInternal functions:\n- negamax(board, depth, alpha, beta, killer_moves, start_time, time_limit) -> int (score)\n- quiescence(board, alpha, beta) -> int (score)\n\nAlgorithm:\n1. Iterative deepening: depth = 1, 2, 3, ... until time runs out\n2. At each depth, run negamax with alpha=-MATE_SCORE, beta=MATE_SCORE\n3. Save best move from each completed depth\n4. Return best move from last completed depth\n\nNegamax alpha-beta:\n- If depth == 0: return quiescence(board, alpha, beta)\n- Generate legal moves (generate_legal_moves)\n- If no moves: return -MATE_SCORE + ply if in check, else 0 (stalemate)\n- Order moves (order_moves with killer_moves)\n- For each move: make_move, score = -negamax(..., depth-1, -beta, -alpha, ...), unmake_move\n- If score >= beta: update killers, return beta (cutoff)\n- If score > alpha: alpha = score, save as best move\n- Return alpha\n\nQuiescence search:\n- stand_pat = evaluate(board)\n- If stand_pat >= beta: return beta\n- If stand_pat > alpha: alpha = stand_pat\n- Generate captures (generate_legal_captures), order (order_captures)\n- For each capture: make_move, score = -quiescence(..., -beta, -alpha), unmake_move\n- Standard alpha-beta on captures\n\nTime management:\n- Check time.time() periodically (every N nodes or at each depth)\n- If time_limit exceeded, raise exception or return early\n- Use try/except pattern: raise TimeoutError when time is up\n\nImport from: src.board (Board), src.movegen (generate_legal_moves, generate_legal_captures), src.evaluation (evaluate, MATE_SCORE), src.move_ordering (order_moves, order_captures, create_killer_table, update_killers)\n\nTests (tests/test_search.py):\n- test_mate_in_1: finds Qh7# or similar obvious mate\n- test_mate_in_2: finds forced mate in 2\n- test_returns_legal_move: search always returns a legal move\n- test_respects_time_limit: completes within 2x time_limit\n- test_deeper_is_better: depth 3 finds better moves than depth 1 in tactical position\n- test_avoids_losing_piece: doesn't hang a queen\n\nRun: python -m pytest tests/test_search.py -v","msg_type":"assign","timestamp":1773174593}